  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Emergency WASH Response for Refugees and Host Communities in Palorinya and Kyaka Ii Settlements</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lack of access to safe water and adequate hygiene and sanitation facilities can lead to the rapid propagation of diseases. Nine cases of cholera were reported in Kyaka II on 29 January 2018, eight of whom were among the new arrivals. The need to stabilize access to safe water through adequate water systems, improve sanitation at household level and institutions, expand health and hygiene education and increase the number of hygiene promoters in the two settlements and nearby host communities is dire. Through this project, IOM in Uganda will provide life-saving, sustainable access to safe water, sanitation and hygiene services to South Sudanese and Congolese refugees in Palorinya and Kyaka II settlements and their host communities in Moyo and Kyegegwa districts respectively.</narrative>
  </description>
